ukc5ovJ15nVNWOHuDJWaMRV82HpN8slaSqkqUQ6Iq6mWDUxaUVmePFk4as7wjoikEvTmXFsKYrO8WxkvSM7-HNHoFYzfi55TeexHMBIkc39YUNoLFvv3vC9FMDMTFIC21WP5hASkFeIqnIWd7hnPRRqFbHYbEQoJrtBbNbs_vCvkkakhN0P02qvqq5lFbiQtcVe24zGRiW-rGR60ervV6fJ5mGSHmubnAPum-FFvFahbLVH-06TXEVkbL9beDUMieVQ275quz0zYDZ5masb6oZ18LyZNHSG1wIk4JEl7DXpR02/hBwGVCvD-xHD3IgET7-Dy1-EdIVwa5aw/19" style="font-size: inherit; color: #00e;" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;!--[if mso]&gt;&lt;table width="580"&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src="https://assets.bwbx.io/images/users/iqjWHBFdfxIU/i4__YjyPDCGc/v0/-1x-1.jpg" alt="The 801st RED HORSE Training Squadron hosted five members of the Royal Canadian Air Force alongside United States Airmen for an airfield Rapid Damage Repair course at Tyndall Air Force Base, Florida. RCAF&amp;amp;#39;s participation served a dual purpose - not only as a training opportunity, but also as a step toward rebuilding a capability that had diminished over decades. Joint efforts like the RDR course highlight the shared commitment to readiness, innovation, and mutual support. Photographer: Patrick Focke&amp;amp;#x2F;US Department of Defense" width="580"/&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;div style="display:none"&gt;&lt;![endif]--&gt;&lt;img alt="第 801 红马训练中队接待了五名加拿大皇家空军成员以及美国空军人员，在佛罗里达州廷德尔空军基地参加了机场快速损坏修复课程。加拿大皇家空军的参与具有双重目的——不仅是一次培训机会，也是重建数十年来衰退能力的一步。 RDR 课程等共同努力凸显了对准备、创新和相互支持的共同承诺。摄影师：帕特里克·福克&amp;amp;#x2F;美国国防部" src="https://assets.bwbx.io/images/users/iqjWHBFdfxIU/i4__YjyPDCGc/v0/-1x-1.jpg" style="width: 100%; display: block; margin-bottom: 4px;" /&gt;&lt;!--[if mso]&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;![endif]--&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;figcaption&gt;&lt;div style="font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.4;"&gt;廷德尔空军基地正在被重建为一个具有超强弹性的“未来设施”。&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;p style="margin-top: 24px; font-size: 16px;"&gt;&lt;strong style="font-size: 16px;"&gt;在皮特·赫格斯领导的五角大楼内&lt;/strong&gt;，气候已经成为一个“肮脏的词”，但这并不意味着军队没有做好&lt;a href="https://links.message.bloomberg.com/a/sc/fnmWGfZgjjstDShtun01NMTshonn3eTGqAHM7sI-cKmSgoqYK